Start
/ Test: change default signing provider via settings, sign+verify still works
/ Note: we can only test with ed25519 in PLang (no DLL loading), but this exercises
/ the settings → provider resolution path. C# tests cover real provider swap with mocks.
- create identity testSigner
- set signing provider to ed25519
- set %data% = { "payload": "swapped" }
- sign %data%, provider ed25519
- verify %data% with contracts ['C0']
- assert %data.Signature.Verified.Success% is true, "sign with explicit provider param should verify"
- assert %data.Signature.Algorithm% equals 'ed25519', "algorithm should reflect provider used"
